text:
この3つどもえで、一番遅いのはトヨタのノアだから面白い。この事実が記事に書かれないから、ビデオ作った奴がバカにされるんだけどね。
日本人は既にトヨタ方式のハイブリッドが良いなんて言う輩はほとんどいないんだけどね。
えーー、トヨタのハイブリッドに乗ってるのーー、よく乗っていられるねって感じだろ。事実、トヨタのハイブリッドから同じハイブリッドに乗り換える奴は殆どいないからね。
理由は、アクセルの動作に反応が遅く、プリウスなどは軽NAと同だから、こんな車に乗ってられるかよ、となる分けね。
この解説者は同じシステムがノアで、136馬力が維持できるからこちらが良いって言いたいんだろ。
LFAが560馬力と書かれていても、実際はたった430馬力しか出せないのと同じで、ノア99馬力のエンジンだと、実際の出力は僅か60馬力程度しかないんだって知ってるよね。
ホラ軽NAと同等、いや、軽以下に成り下がっただろ。
この程度の車が本当に良いかね?

だから、NoGood しか押されない。

こういう奴等が日本人に対しトヨタの売上に悪影響だって気づかないのも、頭がどうなっているんだかね。
要はヘイトメディアの偏向報道と同じだろ。
野党同等の嘘宣伝をしてしる訳よ。　まあ、トヨタを貶めたいなら分かるがね。

i hope this help someone
saludos..
Solution 4: Check your settings
If the keys on the Cover aren’t working, but the touchpad is
Make sure filter keys are turned off in your Ease of Access settings:
Step 1:
From the Start screen, swipe in from the right edge of the screen and tap Search.
(If you're using a mouse, point to the upper-right corner of the screen, move the mouse pointer
down, and then click Search.)
Step 2:
Tap or click the arrow above the search box, and then tap or click Settings.
Step 3:
In the search box, enter filter keys, and in the search results, tap or click Turn filter keys on or off.
Step 4:
Under Filter Keys, make sure that Filter Keys is set to Off.

text:
Chemical reactions:
This assumes that every atheist is a absolute materialist. It even posits a form of materialism no materialist would subscribe to, cause it says: whatever cannot be shown to exist, does not exist.

This is a strawman argument. And strawman arguments discredit every argument for god.

But what is the issue here? How can we have free will (a will independend from deterministic rules)?
First i have to show, that there are facts that are independent from deterministic rules.
Every living self conscious being is proof of a fact that can not be explained by deterministc rules alone.
There is a will free from deterministc rules at work.
And everyone is that will.

I cannot proove how free will is in action, but i can state that a will free from deterministic rules is proven to exist.
So free will is not disproven.

That makes every moral argument based on the absence of free will a baseless argument.

"If you were merely chemical reactions, your life would be meaningless."
Meaning does not depend on dependencies, but on experience. We experience a mind at work, even when we do not know what does the work. But ultimately meaning is created through identity. See next comment.
